# starting_player Path Analysis

## Source Event

`starting_player` is read from game state through:

- `ABOALE.Games.ShootIt.ShootItEventsHandler$$OnStartingPlayerChangeEvent`
- RVA/VA: `0x5111488`

This function reads `change:gs:starting_player`, converts the value to an integer, stores it into a closure field:

- closure field: `ShootItEventsHandler.<>c__DisplayClass89_0.startingPlayer`
- field offset: `0x10`

Then it schedules the callback through `InvokeNextFrame`.

## Callback

- `ShootItEventsHandler.<>c__DisplayClass89_0$$<OnStartingPlayerChangeEvent>b__0`
- RVA/VA: `0x5113C98`

Important instructions:

```asm
0x5113CE0  LDR X8, [X0,#0xB8]
0x5113CE4  LDR X8, [X8,#0x60]     ; static Action<int> OnStartingPlayerValueUpdate
0x5113CEC  LDR W1, [X19,#0x10]    ; closure.startingPlayer
0x5113D04  BR X3                  ; invoke Action<int>
```

So `startingPlayer` is passed to subscribers as an `int`.

## Consumer

- `Jawaker.Games.ShootIt.ShootItGameManager$$OnStartingPlayerValueUpdate`
- RVA/VA: `0x51170E8`

Important instructions:

```asm
0x51171E0  MOV X0, XZR
0x51171E4  BL  0x5105E84          ; get local player index/id
0x51171F8  CMP X8, W19, SXTW      ; compare local player with startingPlayer
0x5117200  CSET W1, NE            ; bool right = localPlayer != startingPlayer
0x5117208  B   0x510A7C4          ; ShootItCoinToss.PlayCoinTossAnimation(bool right)
```

The direct consumer found so far is:

- `Jawaker.Games.ShootIt.ShootItCoinToss$$PlayCoinTossAnimation(bool right)`
- RVA/VA: `0x510A7C4`

## Interpretation

The `starting_player` path currently appears to control the coin-toss/start-side animation. It does not yet prove that this path controls authoritative turn ownership or shot permission.

Likely split:

- server/game state sends `starting_player`
- client reads it and updates local presentation/state
- coin toss animation receives `right = localPlayer != startingPlayer`

